1
00:00:00,876 --> 00:00:07,591
♪♪♪

2
00:00:09,301 --> 00:00:11,136
ALLI:
OH, LOOKING CUTE, GIRL!

3
00:00:11,220 --> 00:00:12,763
OH, THANKS.
I WANTED A LOOK THAT SAYS,

4
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:13,639
"I'M READY TO TAKE ON
THE SCHOOL!"

5
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:15,224
(ALLI GIGGLES)

6
00:00:17,893 --> 00:00:20,270
ALLI:
OH YEAH, DALLAS WENT TO GO
FIND THE KEY.

7
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:22,773
HEY!

8
00:00:26,652 --> 00:00:29,196
CLARE:
AHEM! AHEM! AHEM!

9
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:31,073
HAS THE CANCER SPREAD
TO YOUR LUNGS?

10
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:34,076
CLARE:
NO! I'M STILL IN REMISSION.

11
00:00:34,159 --> 00:00:35,494
I WAS JUST HOPING THAT YOU GUYS
WOULD STOP KISSING

12
00:00:35,577 --> 00:00:36,912
LONG ENOUGH FOR ME
TO GET SOME HUGS?

13
00:00:36,995 --> 00:00:38,413
BRING IT IN.

14
00:00:38,497 --> 00:00:39,039
(CLARE AND JENNA GIGGLE)

15
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:40,499
NO KEY?

16
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:42,501
ONLY THE KEY
TO MY HEART.

17
00:00:42,584 --> 00:00:45,170
ALLI:
OH, YOU CAN PUT THAT ONE BACK
ON YOUR KEYCHAIN, BUD.

18
00:00:45,254 --> 00:00:46,380
CLARE:
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

19
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:48,090
PEOPLE ARE GONNA BE HERE
IN TWO HOURS,

20
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:49,591
AND WE NEED TO GET READY
FOR THE "WELCOME BACK" ASSEMBLY.

21
00:00:49,675 --> 00:00:50,884
(DOORS OPEN,
MUSIC BLARES)

22
00:00:50,968 --> 00:00:52,469
DREW:
HEY, GUYS!

23
00:00:53,971 --> 00:00:55,430
WHY DO YOU ALL LOOK
SO SURPRISED?

24
00:00:55,514 --> 00:00:57,516
ALLI:
(GASPS)

25
00:00:57,599 --> 00:00:59,518
CLARE:
IT'S 6 A.M.!

26
00:00:59,601 --> 00:01:01,937
THIS IS SCHOOL,
YOU'RE DREW TORRES!

27
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:03,063
STUDENT COUNCIL PRESIDENT
DREW TORRES,

28
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:04,857
AND, UH, I COULDN'T SLEEP,

29
00:01:04,940 --> 00:01:05,524
SO INSTEAD OF JUST STARING
AT THE CEILING,

30
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:07,317
I DECIDED TO COME HERE.

31
00:01:07,401 --> 00:01:08,527
ANYWAY, I'VE GOT
THE "WELCOME BACK" ASSEMBLY

32
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:09,403
ALL SET UP.
COME ON!

33
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:10,988
CLARE:
WHAT?!

34
00:01:13,156 --> 00:01:14,783
SOUND SYSTEM... CRANKED!
MAKE ROOM!

35
00:01:14,867 --> 00:01:17,160
VIDEO FEED... READY!

36
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:18,829
UH-HUH, UH...

37
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:20,873
SMOKE MACHINE,

38
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:21,540
AND, EXCUSE ME,
EXCUSE ME, EXCUSE ME!

39
00:01:21,623 --> 00:01:23,125
AND... LIGHT SHOW ON!

40
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:28,088
WOW!
YOU REALLY WENT ALL OUT!

41
00:01:28,172 --> 00:01:29,131
I WANTED TO MAKE
OUR SENIOR YEAR

42
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:29,673
THE BEST ONE
DEGRASSI'S EVER HAD!

43
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:31,091
YOU GUYS IN?

44
00:01:31,175 --> 00:01:32,676
ALL:
YEAH! WOO!

45
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:34,928
(CHANTING)
WOO!

46
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:40,309
♪ Black light,
black lightning ♪

47
00:01:40,392 --> 00:01:41,894
♪ Whoa! ♪

48
00:01:43,979 --> 00:01:45,731
♪ Black light,
black lightning ♪

49
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:46,481
IMOGEN:
HEY! HEY, BECKY!

50
00:01:46,565 --> 00:01:48,066
HI.

51
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:51,153
UM, FUN SUMMER?

52
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:55,991
OH... SORRY.

53
00:01:57,618 --> 00:01:59,119
THAT'S OKAY.

54
00:02:00,287 --> 00:02:01,538
TRISTAN:
IT MUST BE NICE

55
00:02:01,622 --> 00:02:03,707
HAVING YOUR CRUSH LINED UP
FOR THE YEAR.

56
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:05,209
I TOLD YOU,
I'M FOCUSING ON MUSIC,

57
00:02:05,292 --> 00:02:06,627
NOT BOYS.

58
00:02:06,710 --> 00:02:09,046
IS THAT WHY YOU
GOT CONTACTS?

59
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:10,130
SO YOU COULD EXCHANGE
FLIRTY GLANCES AT YOUR CELLO?

60
00:02:10,214 --> 00:02:11,715
SHUT UP!

61
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:13,509
HEY, I...

62
00:02:13,592 --> 00:02:15,177
MILES:
(LAUGHS) JEEZ!

63
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,720
CHEWY, YOU WERE HERE
FOR AN ENTIRE YEAR,

64
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:17,471
IT'S LIKE NONE OF THESE GIRLS
EVEN KNOW YOU.

65
00:02:17,554 --> 00:02:19,097
TRUST ME,

66
00:02:19,181 --> 00:02:20,516
NONE OF THESE GIRLS
ARE WORTH KNOWING.

67
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:22,267
I DON'T KNOW,

68
00:02:22,351 --> 00:02:24,561
THERE MIGHT BE ONE OR TWO
WORTH CHECKING OUT.

69
00:02:24,645 --> 00:02:26,813
(ENERGETIC MUSIC PLAYS)

70
00:02:30,442 --> 00:02:32,402
(STUDENTS APPLAUD)

71
00:02:32,486 --> 00:02:33,487
DREW:
GOOOOD MORNING, DEGRASSI!

72
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:35,364
WELCOME TO THE BEST YEAR
OF YOUR LIFE!

73
00:02:35,447 --> 00:02:36,949
I AM HERE
TO INTRODUCE TO YOU

74
00:02:37,032 --> 00:02:38,367
THE TEAM THAT'S GOING
TO BRING YOU THE RUCKUS!

75
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:40,035
YOUR STUDENT COUNCIL!

76
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:42,120
FIRST UP,
YOUR ATHLETIC REP:

77
00:02:42,204 --> 00:02:43,872
THE MAN WITH THE MUSCLES,
MIKE DALLAS!

78
00:02:45,624 --> 00:02:47,543
(STUDENTS CHEER AND APPLAUD)

79
00:02:47,626 --> 00:02:49,878
DREW:
SHE'S SMART AND SASSY!

80
00:02:49,962 --> 00:02:53,298
YOUR SOCIAL COORDINATOR,
ALLI BHANDARI!

81
00:02:53,382 --> 00:02:56,760
(STUDENTS CHEER
AND APPLAUD)

82
00:02:56,844 --> 00:02:58,679
DREW:
HE PUTS THE FUN
INTO FINANCIAL STATEMENTS:

83
00:02:58,762 --> 00:03:00,264
TREASURER,
CONNOR DELAURIER!

84
00:03:01,765 --> 00:03:03,267
(STUDENTS CHEER AND APPLAUD)

85
00:03:05,269 --> 00:03:07,104
SHE'LL TAKE MINUTES
AND YOUR HEART:

86
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:09,648
SECRETARY,
JENNA MIDDLETON!

87
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:11,400
(STUDENTS CHEER
AND APPLAUD)

88
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:15,863
NEXT UP,
SHE IS MY PARTNER IN CRIME,

89
00:03:15,946 --> 00:03:16,947
THE VOICE IN THE BACK
OF MY MIND,

90
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,532
HER NEW HAIRDO
SURE IS FINE...

91
00:03:20,242 --> 00:03:23,537
YOUR VICE PRESIDENT,
CLARE EDWARDS!

92
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,205
(STUDENTS CHEER
AND APPLAUD)

93
00:03:26,957 --> 00:03:29,168
NOW, FINALLY, FINALLY,

94
00:03:29,251 --> 00:03:31,962
HE'S HANDSOME,
HE'S FUNNY...

95
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:34,047
HE'S ME.

96
00:03:34,131 --> 00:03:36,800
YOUR STUDENT COUNCIL PRESIDENT,
DREW TORRES!

97
00:03:36,884 --> 00:03:38,635
(STUDENTS CHEER
AND APPLAUD)

98
00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:40,220
WELCOME TO DEGRASSI,
EVERYBODY!

99
00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:43,390
TODAY IS A FRESH START
FOR EVERYONE,

100
00:03:43,473 --> 00:03:44,558
INCLUDING ME.

101
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:46,268
THIS YEAR IS ABOUT FUN,

102
00:03:46,351 --> 00:03:47,769
OLD FRIENDS,

103
00:03:47,853 --> 00:03:48,937
NEW DEVELOPMENTS,

104
00:03:49,021 --> 00:03:50,522
ABOUT-

105
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:53,775
(STUDENTS GASP)

106
00:03:53,859 --> 00:03:55,819
ALLI:
UM...

107
00:03:55,903 --> 00:03:57,154
DALLAS: DREW!
ALLI: IS HE OKAY?

108
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:58,572
DALLAS:
DREW!

109
00:03:58,655 --> 00:04:00,324
♪ Whatever it takes ♪

110
00:04:00,407 --> 00:04:02,576
♪ (The best that I can be) ♪

111
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:03,869
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

112
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:07,080
♪ I know I can make it through ♪

113
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:11,877
ALLI:
WELL, THAT WAS AN ASSEMBLY
NO ONE'LL EVER FORGET.

114
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:12,794
CLARE:
I HOPE DREW'S OKAY.

115
00:04:12,878 --> 00:04:14,796
WELL, AFTER HE CAME TO,

116
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,590
I SAW SEVEN GRADE NINE GIRLS
OFFER TO CARRY HIS BOOKS,

117
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:18,467
SO I THINK HE'LL BE FINE.

118
00:04:18,550 --> 00:04:19,218
WELL, UNTIL HIS FIANCEE
COMES HOME FROM UNIVERSITY

119
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:21,553
FOR A VISIT.

120
00:04:21,637 --> 00:04:22,679
JENNA:
SO YOU HAVE PHYSICS
FOURTH PERIOD.

121
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:23,805
UM, I COULD SWITCH
INTO THAT.

122
00:04:23,889 --> 00:04:24,723
BUT YOU KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT PHYSICS.

123
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:25,933
YEAH,
BUT WOULDN'T IT BE FUN

124
00:04:26,016 --> 00:04:27,226
TO HAVE
ALL OUR CLASSES TOGETHER?

125
00:04:27,309 --> 00:04:29,686
BUT IT'S PHYSICS,
IT'S ALREADY FUN.

126
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:31,355
OH, YOU GUYS ONLY HAVE
THREE CLASSES TOGETHER?

127
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:33,106
IT MUST FEEL LIKE
AN OCEAN APART.

128
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,316
JENNA:
YOU'RE STILL THINKING
ABOUT LEO?

129
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:35,901
HE'S IN FRANCE,
LET HIM ROT THERE!

130
00:04:35,984 --> 00:04:38,904
COME ON,
LEO'S A GOOD GUY.

131
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:39,905
WELL, SHE CAN'T BE THINKING
ABOUT HIM THAT HARD

132
00:04:39,988 --> 00:04:41,615
IF SHE'S ALREADY GOT
A DATE TONIGHT.

133
00:04:41,698 --> 00:04:43,659
WELL, JEEZ, YOU MOVE FAST.
IT'S NOT EVEN FIRST PERIOD!

134
00:04:43,742 --> 00:04:45,077
WITH WHO?

135
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,578
SHE WON'T TELL ME!

136
00:04:46,662 --> 00:04:47,829
I JUST DON'T WANT
TO SAY ANYTHING

137
00:04:47,913 --> 00:04:49,414
UNTIL I KNOW FOR SURE
THAT IT'S GONNA WORK OUT.

138
00:04:49,498 --> 00:04:50,958
SO IT'S DALLAS.
IT'S NOT DALLAS!

139
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:53,085
IT'S GOTTA BE DALLAS.
ABOUT TIME!

140
00:04:53,168 --> 00:04:54,503
YEAH, YOU TWO WILL MAKE
THE CUTEST BABIES!

141
00:04:54,586 --> 00:04:55,504
OKAY, JUST LET ME GO
ON MY DATE,

142
00:04:55,587 --> 00:04:56,547
AND IF THERE'S FIREWORKS,

143
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:59,007
THEN YOU GUYS CAN MEET HIM.

144
00:04:59,091 --> 00:05:00,592
OKAY, BUT IF DALLAS
IS IN MY NEXT CLASS,

145
00:05:00,676 --> 00:05:01,301
CAN I MEET HIM THEN?

146
00:05:01,385 --> 00:05:02,886
UGH!

147
00:05:03,512 --> 00:05:05,013
(SIGHS)

148
00:05:06,515 --> 00:05:08,350
I TOLD YOU,
I'M FINE!

149
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:10,269
DUDE, YOU COLLAPSED
ON STAGE!

150
00:05:10,352 --> 00:05:11,228
THE NURSE TOOK
MY BLOOD PRESSURE,

151
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:12,437
DID HER LITTLE TESTS
OR WHATEVER,

152
00:05:12,521 --> 00:05:14,648
I PASSED, I'M-

153
00:05:14,731 --> 00:05:15,816
WHAT MORE DO YOU WANT
FROM ME?

154
00:05:15,899 --> 00:05:17,818
YOU ALSO SAID
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN SLEEPING.

155
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:18,819
SO? DUDE, CAN WE JUST GET
THE SCHOOL YEAR STARTED?

156
00:05:18,902 --> 00:05:19,862
WE'RE GONNA BE LATE
FOR MATH.

157
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:21,446
DALLAS:
HOLD UP.

158
00:05:22,781 --> 00:05:23,615
YOU CAN PRETEND
FOR EVERYONE ELSE,

159
00:05:23,699 --> 00:05:25,200
BUT YOU CAN'T PRETEND
FOR ME.

160
00:05:25,284 --> 00:05:27,536
WHAT?
I COULD LIKE MATH.

161
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:29,496
YOU THINKING ABOUT ADAM?

162
00:05:29,580 --> 00:05:31,081
I'M TRYING NOT TO.

163
00:05:32,374 --> 00:05:34,793
BUT YOU'VE GOTTA SLEEP.

164
00:05:34,877 --> 00:05:36,128
HAVE YOU BEEN TAKING THOSE PILLS
THE DOCTOR GAVE YOU?

165
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:37,462
THE ZOLPIDEM
OR WHATEVER IT'S CALLED?

166
00:05:37,546 --> 00:05:38,589
NO, I DON'T NEED THEM.

167
00:05:38,672 --> 00:05:40,257
YOU NEED SOMETHING.

168
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,509
YEAH, I-I NEED THIS:

169
00:05:42,593 --> 00:05:44,178
SCHOOL, STUDENT COUNCIL,
STUFF TO KEEP ME BUSY,

170
00:05:44,261 --> 00:05:45,762
MAYBE TIRE ME OUT.

171
00:05:47,181 --> 00:05:48,724
FOR THE FIRST TIME
SINCE ADAM DIED,

172
00:05:48,807 --> 00:05:51,643
I'M EXCITED
ABOUT STUFF AGAIN.

173
00:05:51,727 --> 00:05:52,311
EXCEPT MATH CLASS,
RIGHT?

174
00:05:52,394 --> 00:05:54,313
YOU CRAZY?

175
00:05:54,396 --> 00:05:55,647
MR. SIMPSON:
ZOE RIVAS!

176
00:05:55,731 --> 00:05:58,942
A REAL LIVE CELEBRITY
AT OUR SCHOOL!

177
00:05:59,026 --> 00:06:01,153
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT LIKE
GATSBY GARCIA IN REAL LIFE.

178
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:03,530
YOU WATCH "WEST DRIVE"?

179
00:06:03,614 --> 00:06:07,492
OH, NO, NO.
MY SON...

180
00:06:07,576 --> 00:06:09,077
HE LOVES THE SHOW.

181
00:06:10,746 --> 00:06:11,580
I'M GONNA GO
SET YOU UP.

182
00:06:11,663 --> 00:06:13,165
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

183
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:16,210
CAN WE LEAVE NOW?

184
00:06:16,293 --> 00:06:17,252
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

185
00:06:17,336 --> 00:06:18,754
AND I BELIEVE I SAID,

186
00:06:18,837 --> 00:06:20,214
"I DON'T WANNA GO
TO THAT STEAMING HELLHOLE!"

187
00:06:20,297 --> 00:06:21,924
YOU'RE FIFTEEN.

188
00:06:22,007 --> 00:06:23,258
IF YOU'RE NOT WORKING,
YOU HAVE TO BE IN SCHOOL.

189
00:06:23,342 --> 00:06:25,344
BUT THIS ONE?

190
00:06:25,427 --> 00:06:27,930
I SENT YOU TO PARIS
THIS SUMMER,

191
00:06:28,013 --> 00:06:30,182
SO YOU COULD GET TO KNOW
SOME FRIENDS WHO GO HERE.

192
00:06:30,265 --> 00:06:31,683
WHAT IF EVERYONE
FINDS OUT

193
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:33,560
WHY I GOT KICKED OFF
THE SHOW?

194
00:06:33,644 --> 00:06:35,145
OH HONEY, THEY WON'T.

195
00:06:37,773 --> 00:06:39,900
LET'S CALL THIS PARTY
TO ORDER!

196
00:06:39,983 --> 00:06:41,151
ALLI: ALL RIGHT!
CLARE: ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE OKAY?

197
00:06:41,235 --> 00:06:42,361
DREW:
YEAH, I'M FINE.

198
00:06:42,444 --> 00:06:43,695
'CAUSE IT'S OKAY
IF YOU'RE NOT,

199
00:06:43,779 --> 00:06:45,280
YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH A LOT
WITH ADAM AND-

200
00:06:45,364 --> 00:06:47,616
NO, I'M FINE!

201
00:06:47,699 --> 00:06:48,992
YOU KNOW,
I TALKED TO SIMPSON.

202
00:06:49,076 --> 00:06:49,576
HE SAID THAT WE COULD
SPLIT THE WORKLOAD,

203
00:06:49,660 --> 00:06:51,453
IF IT'S TOO MUCH-

204
00:06:51,537 --> 00:06:52,079
CLARE, I'M THE PRESIDENT,
I CAN DO THIS, ALL RIGHT?

205
00:06:52,162 --> 00:06:54,206
S-S-START.

206
00:06:54,289 --> 00:06:55,958
CLARE:
OKAY, UM...

207
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:57,459
BUT WE'RE STILL SHORT
A FEW REPS -

208
00:06:57,543 --> 00:06:59,086
DRAMA, KNITTING SOCIETY,
OUTDOORS CLUB.

209
00:06:59,169 --> 00:07:01,630
DREW:
JUST, UH, BANG THE GAVEL.

210
00:07:01,713 --> 00:07:03,674
OKAY, I'D LIKE CALL TO ORDER
THE FIRST OFFICIAL MEETING

211
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:05,467
OF THIS YEAR'S
STUDENT COUNCIL!

212
00:07:05,551 --> 00:07:07,052
(STUDENTS APPLAUD)

213
00:07:10,055 --> 00:07:11,390
AND I WOULD LIKE TO GET
RIGHT TO THE GOOD STUFF,

214
00:07:11,473 --> 00:07:12,933
PLANNING THE FIRST EVENT
OF THE YEAR.

215
00:07:13,016 --> 00:07:15,143
WE NEED SOMETHING BIG,
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

216
00:07:15,227 --> 00:07:17,271
I WAS THINKING MAYBE A DANCE?

217
00:07:17,354 --> 00:07:18,939
I SECOND THAT!

218
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:21,525
WHAT IF WE DID SOMETHING
TO REMEMBER ADAM?

219
00:07:21,608 --> 00:07:22,985
BECKY:
YEAH, LIKE A "NO TEXTING
AND DRIVING" CAMPAIGN!

220
00:07:23,068 --> 00:07:24,987
FOR THE FIRST EVENT
OF THE YEAR?

221
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:26,697
ALLI:
ALL PEOPLE CAN LEARN
FROM THE TRAGEDY.

222
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:28,073
ADAM WOULD'VE WANTED THIS.

223
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:29,157
NO, HE WOULDN'T HAVE!

224
00:07:29,241 --> 00:07:30,409
HE WOULD'VE WANTED...

225
00:07:30,492 --> 00:07:31,994
A DEGRASSI
"BEACH BASH" DANCE!

226
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:35,122
BECKY:
(SIGHS)

227
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:37,457
LET'S PUT IT
TO THE PEOPLE.

228
00:07:37,541 --> 00:07:38,709
SHALL WE PREPARE PRESENTATIONS

229
00:07:38,792 --> 00:07:40,377
AND TAKE A VOTE
AT TOMORROW'S MEETING?

230
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:41,962
YEAH, I GUESS.

231
00:07:44,214 --> 00:07:45,966
CLARE:
GREAT. UM, NEXT ORDER
OF BUSINESS:

232
00:07:46,049 --> 00:07:48,427
SHOULD WE USE THE GRANT MONEY
TO REVIVE DEGRASSI TV?

233
00:07:49,011 --> 00:07:49,887
YEAH, BUT I LIKED HER
AFTER SHE GOT MAD AT US

